Benefits

Insurance companies face data sprawl with disparate systems and¬error-prone manual processes impeding a holistic view of the business and risk exposure. Gaining this insight is critical at a time when the regulatory environment demands businesses improve their risk models and practices.

Using actuarial statistical analysis and modelling based upon Microsoft solutions, insurance companies are able to better identify risks, price¬policies more effectively, understand their liabilities more accurately,¬and optimise their financial positions.

Faced with exponentially increasing volumes of data, it is challenging for financial institutions to translate that data into insight needed to improve customer profitability and retention. To do this effectively, you need deeper insight into the profitability of you customer portfolio and have the ability to visualise that data so it is actionable.

With Microsoft customer and product analytics solutions, you can capitalise on internal and external data to combine profitability, segmentation and customer preference, to gain a complete end-to-end view of the customer.

Reduce costs

Avoid return visits to the office and customer meeting travel, by making it easy to contact colleagues and find, share, and analyse information - remaining productive, with the full power of the Microsoft Office suite and the familiar Windows 10 interface on a tablet or mobile device.
Improve processes

Enable mobile access to key information for executives and case workers in the field, streamlining their work process, providing more capacity for accuracy whilst improved visibility positively effects related processes.  Remove the potential for diluted detail when ‘reporting back’ to the office by using a ‘live’ mobile app to update notes, improving the integrity and quality of information generated by case workers.
The right device

Gain unmatched choice in size, form-factor, and specialisation (e.g. rugged) devices, as well as an ecosystem of accessory providers (vehicle mounts, stylus, cases, etc.) to deliver Line of Business, (LOB) apps, on built-for-purpose devices. Government Officials and field-based workers are more effective, anywhere, whilst immediate access and updates to CRM, ERP or related business systems translates to faster, more effective citizen services.

Uncompromised security

Mobile devices running Windows embedded or Windows 10 platform are managed with the same tools used to manage desktop and laptop security.  Files can be encrypted and access managed with CESG accredited technology such as Bitlocker and Direct Access VPN.  With the Enterprise Mobility Suite, this can be extended to include non-windows devices also.
Consistent architecture

Microsoft technology is built on a robust and secure permission based architecture.  Microsoft’s mobile solutions adopt this same architecture.  Regardless of the application or any variation in platform or device, permission based security is consistent and persistently maintained.

Reduce requirements and save

Microsoft mobility solutions enable employees to work from anywhere at any time.  ‘Hot Desks’ provide the perfect environment for mobile technology users, offering the capacity for more than one employee to use as a desk space at different times of the day.  The direct effect is a reduction in the amount of office space required and the associated costs.
Create efficiencies

Office space requirements can be directly reduced by adopting a home working policy.  Microsoft maximises home worker productivity with the full suite of Microsoft applications on their mobile device, whilst reducing office space infrastructure and furniture costs as well as rationalising related facilities requirements such as power and heating.  Home workers also offer a compelling, resilient capability, should office space be effected by any form of natural or incidental disaster.
Do more with less

Microsoft empowers a mobile workforce that saves costs in diverse and practical ways.  Travel costs can be directly reduced by negating the need to travel specifically, but there are also more subtle cost efficiencies, such as the reduction in administration costs by being able to update data directly whilst mobile.  A return on investment can be considered to include gains in time and inherent service.
